Assignment 7

As per the instruction I have tried to create a script that will create a table in the specified database.

Requirement
1. Latest version of Python
2. PostgreSQL
3. psycopg2 library

Setup steps
Create a folder
1. mypython_project

2. Create Virtual Environment
python -m venv venv

3. Activate the virtual environment
venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1

4. Install psycopg2 library
pip install psycopg2

5. Create a database in PostgreSQL
CREATE DATABASE myproject_python

6. Update the Database login details in app.py file

7. Run the app.py script
python app.py

Functions
1. get_connection - Check DB Connection.
2. create_table - this will create a table if it is not present.
3. insert - this will help us to add the data into the table.
4. get_all - this function will get all the data from the table.